  "prompt": "When and where was the song Londa Badnam Hua Nasiban Tere Liye originated?",
  "response": "The song \"Londa Badnam Hua Nasiban Tere Liye\" is a playful and humorous Indian folk song that has gained popularity through various renditions, particularly in the Bhojpuri and Hindi-speaking regions. It is often performed at weddings, festivals, and other celebratory events.\n\nThe exact origin of the song is unclear, as it is part of a traditional folk repertoire that has been passed down orally over generations. Folk songs like this often evolve and are adapted by different artists and regions, making it difficult to pinpoint a specific time or place of origin.\n\nThe song gained wider recognition in the 2000s when it was adapted and popularized by Bhojpuri artists, and it has since been featured in various regional films and music albums. Its catchy tune and humorous lyrics have made it a favorite in the folk music scene.",
